aw_title: CTP803 - Servicing and Testing of Gas Pipeline and Equipment
aw_description:
Element one of the works comprises the servicing of gas and oil fired heating equipment, appliances and pressure units.
Element two of the work comprises the annual testing of all gas installations. The service works refers to the following types of installations; School Premises, School Kitchens only and all other corporate buildings. Orders will be issued separately for each establishment and/or kitchen.

The contract is split into two defined geographical lot areas North and South Derbyshire as detailed within the tender documentation.

The award of contract shall be based upon the tendered prices and assessment by the Council as to the capability of the supplier to service the contract to satisfactory standards.
cpv_description: Repair and maintenance services of central heating

aw_title: CPU2961 Independent Living Support (Homelessness Prevention) Service
aw_description:
Nottingham City Council (NCC) was seeking to appoint a suitably experienced and knowledgeable provider(or a similarly qualified consortium of providers) of independent living support for citizens who are homelessor at risk of homelessness. NCC encourages consortium arrangements where it will allows for complementaryknowledge, experience and resources to be drawn upon in order to fully meet the requirements of the service. Itwill be necessary to identify a lead provider who will be responsible for the contract.  
The service is required to prevent homelessness through the provision of timely, targeted and effectivesupport,enabling citizens to maintain their accommodation or obtain other suitable accommodation,consequently lessening the impact of homelessness on their wider wellbeing.

aw_title: CTP803 - Servicing and Testing of Gas Pipeline and Equipment
aw_description:
Element one of the works comprises the servicing of gas and oil fired heating equipment, appliances and pressure units.
Element two of the work comprises the annual testing of all gas installations. The service works refers to the following types of installations; School Premises, School Kitchens only and all other corporate buildings. Orders will be issued separately for each establishment and/or kitchen.

The contract is split into two defined geographical lot areas North and South Derbyshire as detailed within the tender documentation.

The award of contract shall be based upon the tendered prices and assessment by the Council as to the capability of the supplier to service the contract to satisfactory standards.

aw_title: CPU2961 Independent Living Support (Homelessness Prevention) Service
aw_description:
Nottingham City Council (NCC) was seeking to appoint a suitably experienced and knowledgeable provider(or a similarly qualified consortium of providers) of independent living support for citizens who are homelessor at risk of homelessness. NCC encourages consortium arrangements where it will allows for complementaryknowledge, experience and resources to be drawn upon in order to fully meet the requirements of the service. Itwill be necessary to identify a lead provider who will be responsible for the contract.  
The service is required to prevent homelessness through the provision of timely, targeted and effectivesupport,enabling citizens to maintain their accommodation or obtain other suitable accommodation,consequently lessening the impact of homelessness on their wider wellbeing.

aw_title: CPU2961 Independent Living Support (Homelessness Prevention) Service
aw_description:
Nottingham City Council (NCC) was seeking to appoint a suitably experienced and knowledgeable provider(or a similarly qualified consortium of providers) of independent living support for citizens who are homelessor at risk of homelessness. NCC encourages consortium arrangements where it will allows for complementaryknowledge, experience and resources to be drawn upon in order to fully meet the requirements of the service. Itwill be necessary to identify a lead provider who will be responsible for the contract.  
The service is required to prevent homelessness through the provision of timely, targeted and effectivesupport,enabling citizens to maintain their accommodation or obtain other suitable accommodation,consequently lessening the impact of homelessness on their wider wellbeing.

aw_title: CTP803 - Servicing and Testing of Gas Pipeline and Equipment
aw_description:
Element one of the works comprises the servicing of gas and oil fired heating equipment, appliances and pressure units.
Element two of the work comprises the annual testing of all gas installations. The service works refers to the following types of installations; School Premises, School Kitchens only and all other corporate buildings. Orders will be issued separately for each establishment and/or kitchen.

The contract is split into two defined geographical lot areas North and South Derbyshire as detailed within the tender documentation.

The award of contract shall be based upon the tendered prices and assessment by the Council as to the capability of the supplier to service the contract to satisfactory standards.
cpv_description: Repair and maintenance services of central heating

Nottingham City Council (NCC) was seeking to appoint a suitably experienced and knowledgeable provider(or a similarly qualified consortium of providers) of independent living support for citizens who are homelessor at risk of homelessness. NCC encourages consortium arrangements where it will allows for complementaryknowledge, experience and resources to be drawn upon in order to fully meet the requirements of the service. Itwill be necessary to identify a lead provider who will be responsible for the contract.  
The service is required to prevent homelessness through the provision of timely, targeted and effectivesupport,enabling citizens to maintain their accommodation or obtain other suitable accommodation,consequently lessening the impact of homelessness on their wider wellbeing.

aw_title: CTP803 - Servicing and Testing of Gas Pipeline and Equipment
aw_description:
Element one of the works comprises the servicing of gas and oil fired heating equipment, appliances and pressure units.
Element two of the work comprises the annual testing of all gas installations. The service works refers to the following types of installations; School Premises, School Kitchens only and all other corporate buildings. Orders will be issued separately for each establishment and/or kitchen.

The contract is split into two defined geographical lot areas North and South Derbyshire as detailed within the tender documentation.

The award of contract shall be based upon the tendered prices and assessment by the Council as to the capability of the supplier to service the contract to satisfactory standards.
cpv_description: Repair and maintenance services of central heating

aw_title: CPU2961 Independent Living Support (Homelessness Prevention) Service
aw_description:
Nottingham City Council (NCC) was seeking to appoint a suitably experienced and knowledgeable provider(or a similarly qualified consortium of providers) of independent living support for citizens who are homelessor at risk of homelessness. NCC encourages consortium arrangements where it will allows for complementaryknowledge, experience and resources to be drawn upon in order to fully meet the requirements of the service. Itwill be necessary to identify a lead provider who will be responsible for the contract.  
The service is required to prevent homelessness through the provision of timely, targeted and effectivesupport,enabling citizens to maintain their accommodation or obtain other suitable accommodation,consequently lessening the impact of homelessness on their wider wellbeing.

The contract is split into two defined geographical lot areas North and South Derbyshire as detailed within the tender documentation.

The award of contract shall be based upon the tendered prices and assessment by the Council as to the capability of the supplier to service the contract to satisfactory standards.

aw_title: CTP803 - Servicing and Testing of Gas Pipeline and Equipment
aw_description:
Element one of the works comprises the servicing of gas and oil fired heating equipment, appliances and pressure units.
Element two of the work comprises the annual testing of all gas installations. The service works refers to the following types of installations; School Premises, School Kitchens only and all other corporate buildings. Orders will be issued separately for each establishment and/or kitchen.

The contract is split into two defined geographical lot areas North and South Derbyshire as detailed within the tender documentation.

The award of contract shall be based upon the tendered prices and assessment by the Council as to the capability of the supplier to service the contract to satisfactory standards.
cpv_description: Repair and maintenance services of central heating

aw_title: CPU2961 Independent Living Support (Homelessness Prevention) Service
aw_description:
Nottingham City Council (NCC) was seeking to appoint a suitably experienced and knowledgeable provider(or a similarly qualified consortium of providers) of independent living support for citizens who are homelessor at risk of homelessness. NCC encourages consortium arrangements where it will allows for complementaryknowledge, experience and resources to be drawn upon in order to fully meet the requirements of the service. Itwill be necessary to identify a lead provider who will be responsible for the contract.  
The service is required to prevent homelessness through the provision of timely, targeted and effectivesupport,enabling citizens to maintain their accommodation or obtain other suitable accommodation,consequently lessening the impact of homelessness on their wider wellbeing.

NCC encourages consortium arrangements where it will allows for complementaryknowledge, experience and resources to be drawn upon in order to fully meet the requirements of the service. Itwill be necessary to identify a lead provider who will be responsible for the contract.  
The service is required to prevent homelessness through the provision of timely, targeted and effectivesupport,enabling citizens to maintain their accommodation or obtain other suitable accommodation,consequently lessening the impact of homelessness on their wider wellbeing.

Nottingham City Council (NCC) was seeking to appoint a suitably experienced and knowledgeable provider(or a similarly qualified consortium of providers) of independent living support for citizens who are homelessor at risk of homelessness. NCC encourages consortium arrangements where it will allows for complementaryknowledge, experience and resources to be drawn upon in order to fully meet the requirements of the service. Itwill be necessary to identify a lead provider who will be responsible for the contract.  
The service is required to prevent homelessness through the provision of timely, targeted and effectivesupport,enabling citizens to maintain their accommodation or obtain other suitable accommodation,consequently lessening the impact of homelessness on their wider wellbeing.

aw_title: CTP803 - Servicing and Testing of Gas Pipeline and Equipment
aw_description:
Element one of the works comprises the servicing of gas and oil fired heating equipment, appliances and pressure units.
Element two of the work comprises the annual testing of all gas installations. The service works refers to the following types of installations; School Premises, School Kitchens only and all other corporate buildings. Orders will be issued separately for each establishment and/or kitchen.

The contract is split into two defined geographical lot areas North and South Derbyshire as detailed within the tender documentation.

The award of contract shall be based upon the tendered prices and assessment by the Council as to the capability of the supplier to service the contract to satisfactory standards.
cpv_description: Repair and maintenance services of central heating

aw_title: CPU2961 Independent Living Support (Homelessness Prevention) Service
aw_description:
Nottingham City Council (NCC) was seeking to appoint a suitably experienced and knowledgeable provider(or a similarly qualified consortium of providers) of independent living support for citizens who are homelessor at risk of homelessness. NCC encourages consortium arrangements where it will allows for complementaryknowledge, experience and resources to be drawn upon in order to fully meet the requirements of the service. Itwill be necessary to identify a lead provider who will be responsible for the contract.  
The service is required to prevent homelessness through the provision of timely, targeted and effectivesupport,enabling citizens to maintain their accommodation or obtain other suitable accommodation,consequently lessening the impact of homelessness on their wider wellbeing.

aw_title: CTP803 - Servicing and Testing of Gas Pipeline and Equipment
aw_description:
Element one of the works comprises the servicing of gas and oil fired heating equipment, appliances and pressure units.
Element two of the work comprises the annual testing of all gas installations. The service works refers to the following types of installations; School Premises, School Kitchens only and all other corporate buildings. Orders will be issued separately for each establishment and/or kitchen.

The contract is split into two defined geographical lot areas North and South Derbyshire as detailed within the tender documentation.

The award of contract shall be based upon the tendered prices and assessment by the Council as to the capability of the supplier to service the contract to satisfactory standards.
cpv_description: Repair and maintenance services of central heating

Nottingham City Council (NCC) was seeking to appoint a suitably experienced and knowledgeable provider(or a similarly qualified consortium of providers) of independent living support for citizens who are homelessor at risk of homelessness. NCC encourages consortium arrangements where it will allows for complementaryknowledge, experience and resources to be drawn upon in order to fully meet the requirements of the service. Itwill be necessary to identify a lead provider who will be responsible for the contract.  
The service is required to prevent homelessness through the provision of timely, targeted and effectivesupport,enabling citizens to maintain their accommodation or obtain other suitable accommodation,consequently lessening the impact of homelessness on their wider wellbeing.

aw_title: CTP803 - Servicing and Testing of Gas Pipeline and Equipment
aw_description:
Element one of the works comprises the servicing of gas and oil fired heating equipment, appliances and pressure units.
Element two of the work comprises the annual testing of all gas installations. The service works refers to the following types of installations; School Premises, School Kitchens only and all other corporate buildings. Orders will be issued separately for each establishment and/or kitchen.

The contract is split into two defined geographical lot areas North and South Derbyshire as detailed within the tender documentation.

The award of contract shall be based upon the tendered prices and assessment by the Council as to the capability of the supplier to service the contract to satisfactory standards.
cpv_description: Repair and maintenance services of central heating

Nottingham City Council (NCC) was seeking to appoint a suitably experienced and knowledgeable provider(or a similarly qualified consortium of providers) of independent living support for citizens who are homelessor at risk of homelessness. NCC encourages consortium arrangements where it will allows for complementaryknowledge, experience and resources to be drawn upon in order to fully meet the requirements of the service. Itwill be necessary to identify a lead provider who will be responsible for the contract.  
The service is required to prevent homelessness through the provision of timely, targeted and effectivesupport,enabling citizens to maintain their accommodation or obtain other suitable accommodation,consequently lessening the impact of homelessness on their wider wellbeing.

Nottingham City Council (NCC) was seeking to appoint a suitably experienced and knowledgeable provider(or a similarly qualified consortium of providers) of independent living support for citizens who are homelessor at risk of homelessness. NCC encourages consortium arrangements where it will allows for complementaryknowledge, experience and resources to be drawn upon in order to fully meet the requirements of the service. Itwill be necessary to identify a lead provider who will be responsible for the contract.  
The service is required to prevent homelessness through the provision of timely, targeted and effectivesupport,enabling citizens to maintain their accommodation or obtain other suitable accommodation,consequently lessening the impact of homelessness on their wider wellbeing.
